From 5c889c7361eb1181bb521775223e3568c889e32c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 12:51:42 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] lib: translate memcat_p, argv_split to Rust (linux-rs TUs
 16-17)

memcat_p: merge two NULL-terminated void* arrays. C's single reverse-
walking counter with a conditional source-pointer swap
(p = p==b ? &a[nr] : p-1) empirically verified (see /tmp/verify_memcat.c
in the session) to produce order [a..., b..., NULL] before translating,
rather than trusting the pointer arithmetic by inspection -- reimplemented
as two straightforward forward copies producing the same order.

argv_split: whitespace tokenizer. Preserves the C's 'stash the backing
allocation at argv[-1]' trick verbatim so argv_free's pointer arithmetic
(argv--) works identically. New rule 0018: any translated fn whose
kmalloc'd pointer crosses the C ABI to a caller-visible kfree() must use
a raw kmalloc_array shim, NOT kernel::alloc::{KVec,KBox} (different
deallocator) -- these two TUs are its first instances.

New helpers: rust/helpers/ctype.c (isspace, a macro), rust/helpers/slab.c
+= kmalloc_array. Tier-2.5 diff oracle extended: 5,000 argv_split cases +
1,666 memcat_p cases, byte-identical (bench/diff_argv_split.{c,rs}).

Validated: full regression boot green, all symbols confirmed in
System.map from the _rs.o objects.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
